      • createDeactivators

        public void createDeactivators(ConfigFile cfgFile)
        Any of the conditions that evaluated to true when checking whether to load the config file, can later invalidate it (esp. "dateTime"). Therefore, once the ConfigFile has been created, it needs to be provided to the respective deactivators. It is up to them, whether they do something or not (the "OS" is a good example for the latter.
